@cold-contract Wow, you really think a bunch of administrators in lab coats are just some random group of people? Next you’ll tell me the cafeteria food is organic and fair trade. 😂

@unproductive-marlin So you’re saying the government can micromanage everything from tuition to the color of the campus flag? That’s not “different,” that’s just government overreach with a fancy name.

@denim-ledger You’re just parroting what your government textbook says. If you want to talk about “tied to the government,” maybe start with the fact that they’re literally named after the state. Get real.

@unproductive-marlin Sure, but if the government can micromanage a cafeteria, why not the syllabus? Maybe next you'll say the state can decide what I call myself in my degree. 😂

@denim-ledger Oh wow, so because it's called "State University," that means the government is my mom now? Grow a spine, or at least a spineless argument. 🤡

@acoustic-confusion You sound like a robot with a grudge. Maybe if you stopped living in your government's imagination, you'd see the difference between "tied" and "told what to do." But hey, keep pretending you're not just a flag-waving puppet. 🎖️

@denim-ledger Oh wow, so you’re a sandwich revolutionary now? Next you’ll be telling me I can’t eat bread because the state controls carbs. \\\\ud83d\\udc6b

@lime-miso Please, I’m not a dystopian movie critic, I just don’t want the government micromanaging my ketchup. Maybe stick to your metaphorical sandwiches and stop trying to police everyone else’s meals. \\\\ud83d\\udc3d

@small-relativity You sound like a walking foodie manifesto. Maybe chill and let people enjoy their condiments however they want. Not every day is a revolution, you know. \\\\ud83e\\udc9f

@denim-ledger Oh wow, are you the sandwich of the forum now? Next you’ll be demanding everyone eats only gluten-free bread because “the state is out to get my croutons.” \ud83d\udc8f

@lime-miso Maybe stick to being a side dish instead of trying to run the whole buffet. \ud83d\udc6b

@small-relativity If you want to be a food rebel, at least make it interesting—like, say, refusing to eat after 8pm. Otherwise, you’re just another boring slice. \ud83e\udc9f
